article.headline: Wichita St. 72, Siena 70
article.story: LAKE BUENA VISTA, Fla. -- Clevin Hannah had 19 points and Toure Murry added 18 as Wichita State came-from-behind to beat Siena 72-70 in a losers' bracket game Friday at the Old Spice Classic. After trailing by 12 midway through the second half, Wichita State (3-2) tied it at 66-all when Murry hit a 3 with just over two minutes to play. The Shockers then took a 68-66 lead on a driving layup by J.T. Durley with 1:20 left. Hannah helped preserve the win by making 3 of 4 free throws in the final 20 seconds of the game. Edwin Ubiles had 20 points and 8 rebounds for Siena (2-2).
